  <popularWalkingRoutes><![CDATA[<h3>Zug River Stroll</h3>
<ul>
<li>Easy walk</li>
</ul>
<p>Enjoy a relaxing stroll along the impressive river Zug. See local places of interest such as the fishing lake, where the water is so clear you can watch the trout swim and Lech's forest swimming pool. With unique scenery, such as ancient rock formations, forests and glacially-sculpted mountains.</p>
<h3>Zursersee</h3>
<ul>
<li>Moderate walk</li>
<li>8.2km</li>
<li>Expect to take around three to four hours</li>
</ul>
<p>The route begins from the nearby town of Zurs, and ascends up to the scenic lake Zurs. Nestled in a high mountain bowl, you get superb panoramic views over the colourful Lech Valley.</p>
<h3>Tannberg Trail</h3>
<ul>
<li>Moderate trail</li>
<li>9km</li>
<li>Family friendly</li>
</ul>
<p>Discover the tale of the Arlberg's first settlers, the ancient Walser people. This incredible walk will take you on beautiful riverside paths and up onto the green hills with breathtaking views across the valley and its natural treasures.</p>]]></popularWalkingRoutes>
